The paper deals with mobile-edge computing (MEC) networks, which are a subset of wireless networks. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also involves resource allocation and optimization, which are common topics in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which are common topics in cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm to reduce complexity, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
